# Idle Forest — agent rules

Follow the repo root instructions:

- `AGENTS.md` — core workflow, scope, completion checklist
- `AGENTS_UNITY.md` — read before any Unity/scene/prefab/Inspector/serialized-data work

Unity-specific requirements:

- Prefer small, targeted diffs; match nearby code patterns.
- Do not rename or retype serialized Inspector fields unless explicitly requested.
- Do not manually edit `.meta`, `.unity`, `.prefab`, or `.asset` unless the task requires it.
- If Unity Editor setup is needed, describe Inspector steps clearly instead of guessing.
- When Unity MCP is available, query editor state before assuming scene/prefab configuration.
- Before finishing, report changed files, serialized-data risks, and tests/checks run (or why not).
